WEBVTT

00:03.254 --> 00:10.095
[EERIE MUSIC PLAYING]

01:22.208 --> 01:23.501
[CAT YOWLING]

01:24.961 --> 01:25.712
Henrietta.

01:28.381 --> 01:29.340
Henrietta.

01:30.550 --> 01:31.551
Henrietta.

01:35.221 --> 01:37.140
Where are you, child?

01:44.064 --> 01:48.443
[MUFFLED MUSIC PLAYING]

01:48.443 --> 01:50.820
Henrietta. You down there?

01:55.325 --> 01:58.536
[MUSIC PLAYING]

01:58.536 --> 02:03.249
[INDISTINCT EERIE VOICE]

02:26.439 --> 02:27.732
[MUSIC STOPS]

02:33.988 --> 02:38.159
How could you do such a thing to
one of God's innocent creatures?

02:38.159 --> 02:39.160
Answer me!

02:42.705 --> 02:44.666
And on your birthday
of all days.

02:46.876 --> 02:50.213
You have committed
a very grave sin, Henrietta.

02:50.213 --> 02:53.258
And you deserve
a terrible punishment.

02:53.258 --> 02:57.595
Therefore, you are going
to remain here in the dark

02:57.595 --> 02:59.472
until I say you've had enough.

03:01.474 --> 03:05.103
And pray the Lord
to have mercy on your soul.

03:14.654 --> 03:15.405
[DOOR BANGS]

03:33.923 --> 03:35.842
Boy, I just don't know
what to do.

03:37.927 --> 03:39.304
Something's come over her.

03:39.304 --> 03:42.682
It's like she were under
a spell or a curse.

03:42.682 --> 03:46.686
How can you say that?
She's just a little girl, Sam.

03:46.686 --> 03:47.687
Our only child.

03:55.820 --> 03:58.573
Holy Christ.
What's come over her?

04:01.951 --> 04:04.996
[DOGS BARKING]

04:04.996 --> 04:06.831
[MUSIC PLAYING]

04:06.831 --> 04:12.253
[INDISTINCT EERIE VOICE]

04:30.521 --> 04:34.192
[CREAKING]

05:00.843 --> 05:02.303
[SCREAMING]

05:06.099 --> 05:08.101
Sam, what happened?

05:13.523 --> 05:14.899
[SCREAMS]

05:17.610 --> 05:18.945
Oh, my God!

05:23.199 --> 05:26.786
[CREAKING]

05:57.066 --> 05:57.775
No.

06:00.194 --> 06:00.903
No.

06:12.081 --> 06:14.375
[EERIE MUSIC PLAYING]

06:30.767 --> 06:33.561
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING]

07:02.465 --> 07:04.425
[STATIC]

07:04.425 --> 07:07.220
PAUL: Roger, Sherry.
Just a little static.

07:07.220 --> 07:08.888
Listen, I can appreciate

07:08.888 --> 07:10.723
but your feelings about
Simon le Bon...

07:10.723 --> 07:13.601
Jesus, you've been talking
about him for about a week now.

07:13.601 --> 07:16.687
Listen, how does your boyfriend
feel about him?

07:16.687 --> 07:18.773
Sherry, I gotta take a call.
I'll be back.

07:18.773 --> 07:19.982
This is K1UR signing off.

07:21.818 --> 07:23.653
- Hello?
-Hi.

07:23.653 --> 07:26.823
Hi. I thought
you'd be here by now.

07:26.823 --> 07:29.659
I got held up at the library.
I'll see you later.

07:29.659 --> 07:31.160
<i>Later,
what do you mean, "later"?</i>

07:31.160 --> 07:32.995
Listen, if you're doing
something you shouldn't be,

07:32.995 --> 07:35.206
remember, you might
lose your scholarship.

07:35.206 --> 07:37.542
I know, it's back to taking
tourists around Amsterdam,

07:37.542 --> 07:39.210
I'm not that stupid.

07:39.210 --> 07:41.921
Okay, okay,
sorry, I mentioned it.

07:41.921 --> 07:45.049
- I made chili.
-Keep it hot.

07:45.049 --> 07:46.634
I'll be there
in about two hours.

07:46.634 --> 07:48.219
<i>Right.</i>

07:48.219 --> 07:51.055
- And another thing,
<i>- Yeah?</i>

07:51.055 --> 07:52.223
Keep yourself hot, too.

08:00.440 --> 08:04.569
<i>K1UR, this is WA1ZLQ calling.
You got a copy?</i>

08:04.569 --> 08:06.612
Yeah, I copy, John.

08:06.612 --> 08:08.364
Hey, did you find out
who's more popular in Denver?

08:08.364 --> 08:10.324
Kim Basinger or Kelly LeBrock?

08:10.324 --> 08:11.784
<i>It's neck and neck.</i>

08:11.784 --> 08:14.036
<i>Hey, why don't you
ask your computer, man.</i>

08:14.036 --> 08:17.582
<i>By the way, Paul, how are your
data processing exams going?</i>

08:17.582 --> 08:19.959
Well, I could use
a little help from Kelly.

08:19.959 --> 08:23.171
Listen, John, I got some things
I gotta do.

08:23.171 --> 08:24.672
I'll get back to you tonight
after the Celtics game.

08:26.716 --> 08:28.926
This is K1UR signing off.

08:28.926 --> 08:31.679
<i>Okay, catch you later.
This is WA1ZLQ.</i>

08:38.811 --> 08:40.188
A penny for your thoughts.

08:45.860 --> 08:48.988
Something really weird
happened last night.

08:48.988 --> 08:50.031
Okay, out with it.

08:51.991 --> 08:55.912
Well, it was about 11:30,
I was trying to reach Denver.

08:55.912 --> 08:57.788
Where, all of a sudden,
the radio just went crazy.

08:57.788 --> 08:59.582
I mean, completely crazy.

08:59.582 --> 09:01.751
So what's so weird about that?

09:01.751 --> 09:03.503
'Cause it never happened before.

09:03.503 --> 09:06.214
I mean, all the circuits
just went haywire.

09:06.214 --> 09:07.673
And then, all of a sudden,

09:07.673 --> 09:10.551
I heard this voice
calling for help.

09:10.551 --> 09:12.053
And then a terrible scream.

09:12.053 --> 09:13.888
I mean,
a really terrible scream.

09:13.888 --> 09:16.766
- Who was it?
-I don't know.

09:16.766 --> 09:20.686
But whoever it was, he sounded
really scared to death.

09:22.772 --> 09:25.983
I'm starving,
I'm gonna get some chili.

09:25.983 --> 09:28.110
Get me some too, will you?

09:28.110 --> 09:30.238
- Okay.
-Extra jalapeÃ±o.

09:34.992 --> 09:37.703
Damn, I was supposed
to call K7ET.

09:46.671 --> 09:50.466
K1UR calling K7ET.
You got a copy. Come on, back.

09:50.466 --> 09:54.345
[STATIC]

09:58.349 --> 10:00.393
Let's try 1790 MHZ.

10:01.894 --> 10:04.772
[BEEPING]

10:07.233 --> 10:08.609
[HIGH-PITCHED WHINING]

10:11.028 --> 10:15.199
[GROWLING]

10:17.660 --> 10:18.661
Martha, come here, quick.

10:20.705 --> 10:21.414
Come here.

10:22.790 --> 10:23.541
Get me that tape recorder.

10:26.627 --> 10:27.587
Quick.

10:33.009 --> 10:34.010
<i>MAN:
Who are you?</i>

10:35.845 --> 10:36.762
<i>What do you want?</i>

10:38.639 --> 10:39.849
<i>For God's sakes...</i>

10:41.559 --> 10:42.977
<i>Somebody help me.</i>

10:43.936 --> 10:44.937
<i>Help!</i>

10:47.982 --> 10:48.691
<i>Help!</i>

10:50.192 --> 10:52.111
[SCREAMING]

10:57.158 --> 11:01.037
[WOMAN SCREAMING]

11:01.871 --> 11:03.623
[EERIE MUSIC PLAYING]

11:03.623 --> 11:06.292
[INDISTINCT EERIE VOICE]

11:21.307 --> 11:22.183
[STATIC]

11:24.810 --> 11:29.690
<i>K7ET calling K1VR.
Can you hear me, Paul? Over.</i>

11:29.690 --> 11:32.193
- Yeah, I copy.
<i>- It's about time.</i>

11:32.193 --> 11:34.612
<i>I've been trying to raise you
on any number of channels.</i>

11:34.612 --> 11:36.572
<i>Uh, you got a glitch
or just choking the chicken?</i>

11:38.949 --> 11:40.409
Could it be
some stupid HAM operator

11:40.409 --> 11:41.285
playing a practical joke?

11:42.870 --> 11:46.123
No one would pull a stunt
like that. It's unethical.

11:46.123 --> 11:49.460
- Besides it sounded real to me.
-Yeah. Real.

11:54.256 --> 11:55.716
<i>Somebody help me.</i>

11:56.884 --> 11:59.804
<i>Help!</i>

11:59.804 --> 12:01.472
That's enough, Paul.
Please turn it off.

12:03.974 --> 12:05.518
I think
we should call the police.

12:05.518 --> 12:07.186
Yeah, and tell them what?

12:07.186 --> 12:10.356
Hey, isn't any way you can
track down those voices.

12:10.356 --> 12:12.191
Find out where they came from.

12:12.191 --> 12:14.860
You mean, find the radio
that transmitted the signal?

12:14.860 --> 12:16.612
Yeah, I guess.

12:16.612 --> 12:19.865
Hypothetically it's possible,
but it's tough.

12:19.865 --> 12:21.200
First I have to feed

12:21.200 --> 12:23.202
the pile of frequency data
into the computer,

12:23.202 --> 12:25.788
compare
the sound wave variables,

12:25.788 --> 12:27.957
calculate the distances
before I...

12:27.957 --> 12:31.544
Okay, okay. Just do it.
I'll make some coffee.

12:31.544 --> 12:32.545
Make it strong.

12:51.147 --> 12:53.190
MARTHA: You couldn't let me
sleep a little longer?

12:53.190 --> 12:57.153
We gotta find that radio,
a crime could've been committed.

12:57.153 --> 12:58.154
Maybe even murder.

13:00.322 --> 13:01.532
I hope your computer
got it right.

13:34.857 --> 13:36.901
Is it much further?

13:36.901 --> 13:39.195
I don't think so.
The signal's getting stronger.

13:48.287 --> 13:49.121
Hey, watch out.

13:50.581 --> 13:51.874
Why doesn't he
get out of the way?

13:54.460 --> 13:55.211
Asshole.

13:58.005 --> 14:01.008
I can take the abuse
as long as I don't have to walk.

14:01.008 --> 14:03.552
You guys got room in there
for all of me?

14:03.552 --> 14:04.553
Sure.

14:05.805 --> 14:07.932
Get in the back.

14:07.932 --> 14:11.936
Thanks. You know, hitch is fun.
It's the hiking part that sucks.

14:24.156 --> 14:25.699
Massachusetts sucks too, huh?

14:30.329 --> 14:32.706
Come to think of it,
just about every place sucks.

14:38.963 --> 14:41.257
[WHISTLING]

14:42.925 --> 14:46.095
Hey, you guys believe in ghosts?

14:46.095 --> 14:47.805
- No.
-HITCHHIKER: Well, I do.

14:54.144 --> 14:55.229
[SCREAMING]

14:55.229 --> 14:57.481
[LAUGHING]

14:57.481 --> 14:59.817
Quit it. Would you quit it?

15:02.736 --> 15:04.113
Great stuff, huh?

15:04.113 --> 15:05.114
Will you cut the crap?

15:22.214 --> 15:22.965
So long.

15:24.258 --> 15:25.009
PAUL: All right.

15:31.849 --> 15:33.976
You should believe
in ghosts, pea brain.

15:41.567 --> 15:43.736
Son of a bitch.

15:43.736 --> 15:46.614
He stole $5 off me
with that stupid trick.

15:46.614 --> 15:48.115
Are you sure?

15:48.115 --> 15:50.117
Yeah, it was right here
in my pocket.

15:50.117 --> 15:53.621
I bet he rips people off
all the time with that thing.

15:53.621 --> 15:54.371
[BEEPS]

16:01.670 --> 16:02.421
What?

16:03.505 --> 16:04.548
This is it.

16:07.092 --> 16:09.428
Radio message had to come
from that house.

16:09.428 --> 16:13.432
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

16:13.432 --> 16:15.017
[SCREAMS]

16:15.017 --> 16:17.019
Nobody lives there any more.
Just rats.

16:17.019 --> 16:18.896
We were just looking around.

16:18.896 --> 16:19.813
Where are you from?

16:21.148 --> 16:23.067
Boston. We're from Boston.

16:23.067 --> 16:25.069
What are you snooping around
here for anyhow?

16:25.069 --> 16:28.238
Well, we were looking for
a place to rent for the summer.

16:28.238 --> 16:30.324
You see, I'm in data processing
over at...

16:30.324 --> 16:31.075
What the hell is that?

16:32.326 --> 16:33.077
Computers.

16:34.745 --> 16:35.704
[SCOFFS] Computers.

16:43.671 --> 16:45.756
He's really scary.

16:45.756 --> 16:49.051
I thought, I don't know,
he was going to attack us.

16:49.051 --> 16:52.012
You got some imagination.
Just a bum.

16:52.012 --> 16:54.390
Okay, but why did he say
we were snooping?

16:54.390 --> 16:55.808
We just got here.

17:20.833 --> 17:24.044
PAUL: Maybe that guy was right.
Really does look deserted.

17:24.044 --> 17:25.963
Do you mean we came all this way
for nothing?

17:42.021 --> 17:43.022
Paul.

17:45.357 --> 17:50.529
Paul, I don't like this place.
It's depressing.

17:50.529 --> 17:53.490
There's something evil
about the house.

17:53.490 --> 17:57.870
An evil aura.
Let's get out of here, please.

17:57.870 --> 17:59.872
Come on, don't be silly.

19:08.232 --> 19:10.609
Martha. Let's try
upstairs, okay.

19:46.145 --> 19:46.854
MARTHA: Listen.

19:48.355 --> 19:53.694
[BEEPING]

20:14.590 --> 20:15.799
So the computer was right.

20:23.140 --> 20:25.142
An Yaesu FT, for Christ's sakes.

20:27.603 --> 20:30.314
[STATIC]

20:52.002 --> 20:53.337
What are you doing up here?

20:57.674 --> 20:59.134
I said,
what are you doing up here?

20:59.134 --> 21:00.636
Nothing.

21:00.636 --> 21:03.472
We were just looking for that.

21:03.472 --> 21:05.390
Oh, yeah? It's mine.

21:05.390 --> 21:07.768
- You live here?
-No.

21:07.768 --> 21:09.394
We're here on vacation.

21:09.394 --> 21:12.064
My Camper's parked
out in the yard.

21:12.064 --> 21:14.149
I'm here with my brother
and his girlfriend.

21:14.149 --> 21:15.776
Our sister, Tina's with us too.

21:15.776 --> 21:17.027
My name's Jim Dalon.

21:17.027 --> 21:18.946
Well, what about this?

21:18.946 --> 21:21.240
Well, since the house was empty,

21:21.240 --> 21:22.783
I didn't think
anybody would mind.

21:22.783 --> 21:24.159
Get good reception up here.

21:24.159 --> 21:26.119
Hey, who are you?

21:26.119 --> 21:27.746
Just a HAM operator.
Like yourself.

21:30.374 --> 21:31.959
You mind listening to this
for a second.

21:43.387 --> 21:44.346
<i>MAN:
Who are you?</i>

21:46.181 --> 21:46.890
<i>What do you want?</i>

21:48.809 --> 21:50.227
<i>For God's sakes...</i>

21:51.728 --> 21:53.021
<i>Somebody help me.</i>

21:54.398 --> 21:55.107
<i>Help!</i>

21:58.151 --> 21:58.902
<i>Help!</i>

22:00.237 --> 22:02.322
[SCREAMING]

22:03.824 --> 22:07.869
[WOMAN SCREAMING]

22:09.079 --> 22:10.872
[EERIE MUSIC PLAYING]

22:10.872 --> 22:14.334
[INDISTINCT EERIE VOICE]

22:14.334 --> 22:16.712
Well, what do you think?

22:16.712 --> 22:18.380
We're thinking
it all came from here.

22:18.380 --> 22:19.423
I don't get it.

22:21.174 --> 22:23.093
It was your voice.
You can't deny that.

22:23.093 --> 22:25.554
Okay, so it was my voice.

22:25.554 --> 22:28.265
And the scream
sound like my sister, Tina.

22:28.265 --> 22:30.142
It doesn't
make any sense though.

22:30.142 --> 22:33.645
I swear, I don't get it.
When did you tape that?

22:33.645 --> 22:36.857
Last night about 11:30.

22:36.857 --> 22:38.734
No way.

22:38.734 --> 22:40.902
I did bring
the radio up here yesterday.

22:40.902 --> 22:43.864
But I didn't turn it on.
We went to bed early.

22:43.864 --> 22:45.532
Come on, who're you kidding?

22:45.532 --> 22:48.076
I'm not. Look, I can prove it.

22:48.076 --> 22:50.620
I still have to set the aerial
up on the roof.

22:50.620 --> 22:52.706
Come on, let's go take a look.

22:52.706 --> 22:53.707
Wait here.

23:07.512 --> 23:10.599
[INDISTINCT EERIE VOICE]

24:14.538 --> 24:15.664
[MUSIC STOPS]

24:42.190 --> 24:43.400
[SCREAMS]

25:03.211 --> 25:05.589
[CREAKING]

25:15.557 --> 25:18.185
- Turn the motor off.
-What?

25:18.185 --> 25:22.522
Susan, turn the damn motor off,
will you? Geez.

25:22.522 --> 25:23.982
[SCREAMING]

25:23.982 --> 25:25.233
What the hell was that?

25:25.233 --> 25:27.444
[SCREAMING CONTINUES]

25:32.449 --> 25:33.450
PAUL: Martha?

25:36.286 --> 25:37.454
Where are you?

25:37.454 --> 25:39.623
JIM: Over here, here she is.

25:39.623 --> 25:40.373
Martha.

25:44.419 --> 25:47.756
Jesus Christ.
You're bleeding, what happened?

25:49.925 --> 25:52.761
- Oh, Paul, it was horrible.
-What was? Come on.

25:52.761 --> 25:54.638
Over there, the washing machine.

25:59.601 --> 26:00.602
Wait a minute.

26:12.614 --> 26:13.990
Wait a minute.

26:13.990 --> 26:17.577
All right. What the hell
happened down here?

26:17.577 --> 26:19.829
Please take me out of here.

26:19.829 --> 26:21.498
- Okay.
-I'm really scared.

26:21.498 --> 26:24.042
Put your arm around me.
Give me some light, okay.

26:24.042 --> 26:25.585
You're gonna be all right.

26:25.585 --> 26:26.711
Come on.
Let's get you settled down.

26:28.380 --> 26:30.090
Easy. Easy.

26:33.301 --> 26:35.762
Paul's telling the truth.

26:35.762 --> 26:38.431
I listened to that tape, myself,
about 20 times.

26:38.431 --> 26:41.268
It doesn't mean anything.
It's just a bunch of nonsense.

26:41.268 --> 26:42.852
Yeah, right.

26:42.852 --> 26:44.980
And so is what happened
to Martha in the cellar.

26:44.980 --> 26:46.273
But it did happen.

26:53.113 --> 26:54.948
Maybe
there's something supernatural

26:54.948 --> 26:56.449
about all this, guys.

26:56.449 --> 26:59.411
I don't know.
All I know are computers.

26:59.411 --> 27:00.912
I just feel like
we're in some kind of danger

27:00.912 --> 27:02.247
and we've got to do something.

27:02.247 --> 27:05.667
Come on, you've seen
too many horror movies.

27:05.667 --> 27:07.043
Same old bitch and know-it-all.

27:07.043 --> 27:09.212
Always contradicting everything
anybody says.

27:09.212 --> 27:10.589
You wanna mind
your own beeswax,

27:10.589 --> 27:12.257
-you little brat or else...
-Or else what?

27:12.257 --> 27:13.717
Or else.

27:13.717 --> 27:16.177
For Christ's sake,
will you cut it out?

27:16.177 --> 27:18.138
We got enough trouble as is
around here.

27:22.809 --> 27:26.646
Okay. I'm with you. We gotta
get to the bottom of this.

27:26.646 --> 27:27.772
You got any ideas?

27:29.399 --> 27:31.484
My radio's in the truck.

27:31.484 --> 27:34.863
All I can think of is
we tune in to 1790 MHZ,

27:34.863 --> 27:38.700
we listen all night, say about,
two or three miles from here.

27:38.700 --> 27:40.201
- Me too?
-Right.

27:40.201 --> 27:41.828
You tune in
to the same frequency

27:41.828 --> 27:43.580
but don't send any messages.

27:43.580 --> 27:44.748
- You got it?
-Got it.

27:44.748 --> 27:45.665
What do you think will happen?

27:46.750 --> 27:47.667
We'll see.

27:48.877 --> 27:50.378
Feel like keeping me company?

27:51.796 --> 27:54.215
I don't want
to go back to Boston.

27:54.215 --> 27:55.634
Okay, let's get organized.

28:08.855 --> 28:11.316
By the way, Tina,
why didn't you tell us

28:11.316 --> 28:12.901
that you went over the wall
at school?

28:12.901 --> 28:15.028
I asked the headmistress
for permission.

28:15.028 --> 28:17.906
Bullshit. I just talked to her
an hour ago.

28:17.906 --> 28:19.282
- But, I...
-Tina.

28:19.282 --> 28:21.201
If there's something
that really pisses me off,

28:21.201 --> 28:22.994
it's your constant lying.

28:22.994 --> 28:24.579
It's like you get
some perverted pleasure

28:24.579 --> 28:25.288
out of making things up.

28:26.956 --> 28:31.044
Idiots. You're all against me.
I hate you!

28:31.044 --> 28:32.003
I hate you all!

28:33.171 --> 28:34.506
I hate you.

28:40.428 --> 28:45.016
[STATIC]

28:50.105 --> 28:50.855
Is it okay?

28:52.982 --> 28:55.777
Yeah, it's okay.
We just have to wait.

29:01.908 --> 29:05.578
[BEEPING]

29:05.578 --> 29:06.788
You think it will work?

29:08.415 --> 29:09.416
I don't know.

29:12.335 --> 29:14.838
Maybe we never should've
come here.

29:14.838 --> 29:15.797
This house is weird.

29:17.632 --> 29:20.635
It's like something really
horrible happened here once.

29:20.635 --> 29:23.012
Oh, you just think that
'cause nobody lives here.

29:23.012 --> 29:24.806
Empty houses are always creepy.

29:24.806 --> 29:26.558
Oh, yeah.

29:26.558 --> 29:28.351
Well, how come
no one does live here?

29:32.939 --> 29:35.358
Nothing's gonna happen.
This is getting boring.

29:37.485 --> 29:38.778
It's already 11:04.

29:46.244 --> 29:47.203
[SWITCHES OFF RADIO]

29:54.169 --> 29:55.879
[BEEPING]

29:56.963 --> 29:58.757
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

29:58.757 --> 30:02.218
[INDISTINCT EERIE VOICE]

30:26.034 --> 30:29.621
[BEEPING]

30:34.709 --> 30:37.962
[EVIL LAUGHTER]

30:37.962 --> 30:39.047
Oh, my God, what was that?

30:40.924 --> 30:43.468
[EVIL LAUGHTER CONTINUES]

30:45.428 --> 30:46.888
Listen, you stay here.

30:46.888 --> 30:48.515
I'm going downstairs
to take a look.

31:03.822 --> 31:04.864
[SIGHS SOFTLY]

31:34.602 --> 31:36.437
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

31:36.437 --> 31:39.566
[INDISTINCT EERIE VOICE]

32:07.260 --> 32:11.890
[INDISTINCT EERIE VOICE]

32:32.744 --> 32:33.745
Who are you?

32:35.788 --> 32:36.539
What do you want?

32:39.751 --> 32:40.501
For God's sakes...

32:42.378 --> 32:43.671
Somebody help me.

32:44.923 --> 32:45.924
Help!

32:48.927 --> 32:49.677
Help!

32:51.596 --> 32:55.391
[SCREAMING]

33:01.898 --> 33:04.025
That was Jim.

33:04.025 --> 33:05.652
Incredible.
Just like the other night.

33:07.904 --> 33:08.613
Jim!

33:10.281 --> 33:11.991
Jim! Answer me!

33:20.249 --> 33:20.959
Oh, no.

33:22.543 --> 33:23.294
No.

33:30.593 --> 33:31.344
No.

33:38.685 --> 33:43.898
[SCREAMING]

33:43.898 --> 33:44.899
Come on, let's go.

34:00.832 --> 34:02.917
[GROWLING]

34:08.589 --> 34:09.924
[BARKING]

34:14.137 --> 34:17.264
[GROWLING]

34:17.264 --> 34:23.146
[INDISTINCT EERIE VOICE]

34:27.400 --> 34:28.400
[THUDDING]

34:53.509 --> 34:55.178
TINA: Mark! Help!

35:04.437 --> 35:05.730
Mark! Help!

35:12.904 --> 35:14.363
Mark! Help!

35:15.323 --> 35:16.741
Help! Mark!

35:34.217 --> 35:36.094
Get in the camper now.
Lock the door.

36:23.099 --> 36:23.808
MARK: Help!

36:25.101 --> 36:25.810
Help!

36:27.603 --> 36:28.729
SUSAN: Mark!

36:28.729 --> 36:29.730
Help!

36:31.232 --> 36:31.941
Help!

36:45.663 --> 36:47.248
Jesus Christ.
Mark, you're hurt.

36:47.248 --> 36:48.332
It's all right. I'll be okay.

36:52.670 --> 36:54.046
Look, it's that man.

36:55.423 --> 36:56.174
What happened?

36:58.176 --> 37:00.178
MARK: The guy was attacking Tina
with an ax.

37:00.178 --> 37:02.054
Thank God I got there in time.

37:02.054 --> 37:04.182
She's safe inside the camper.

37:04.182 --> 37:05.433
You're losing
a lot of blood, Mark.

37:05.433 --> 37:06.976
We gotta get you
to the hospital.

37:06.976 --> 37:08.895
We'll turn him over
to the police.

37:08.895 --> 37:10.938
- Where's Jim?
-I don't know.

37:10.938 --> 37:13.441
We got separated.
We heard these weird noises

37:13.441 --> 37:16.777
like laughing
coming from the first floor.

37:16.777 --> 37:17.820
He took off to check it out.

37:24.493 --> 37:25.244
Jim?

37:26.996 --> 37:27.955
Jim?

37:30.750 --> 37:31.459
Jim.

37:42.678 --> 37:45.181
MARTHA: Help! Hurry!

37:45.181 --> 37:46.182
Paul!

37:50.561 --> 37:53.022
- Are you all right?
-Yeah, sure.

38:02.323 --> 38:03.324
He went that way.

38:05.076 --> 38:05.826
Damn it.

38:19.840 --> 38:22.301
- He just got by us.
-Forget it.

38:22.301 --> 38:23.261
He's gone now.

38:29.892 --> 38:32.687
- Did you tell Tina about Jim?
-Yeah.

38:32.687 --> 38:34.772
You think she'll be okay?

38:34.772 --> 38:37.441
I gave her a tranquilizer.
She's asleep.

38:37.441 --> 38:38.734
Don't worry, I'll stay with her.

38:38.734 --> 38:40.069
Come on, Mark, let's go.

38:46.867 --> 38:48.619
Lock yourself inside the camper.

38:48.619 --> 38:50.496
Don't open the door
for any reason

38:50.496 --> 38:51.539
until I get back
with the police.

38:51.539 --> 38:52.498
Okay.

39:09.557 --> 39:12.768
Listen, I know who did it.

39:15.771 --> 39:19.317
I saw her.
I saw her plain as day.

39:19.317 --> 39:21.485
Tina, what are you
talking about?

39:21.485 --> 39:25.364
The girl in the white dress.
She was down in the cellar.

39:25.364 --> 39:26.324
Near Jim.

39:27.742 --> 39:30.453
- She had this weird doll.
-Doll?

39:30.453 --> 39:32.288
Yeah, it was like
they understood each other.

39:32.288 --> 39:35.291
I don't know.
Then I heard that song.

39:35.291 --> 39:36.459
That stupid song.

39:38.044 --> 39:40.296
Was it like
a children's nursery rhyme?

39:40.296 --> 39:41.547
Then you believe me?

39:41.547 --> 39:43.382
Oh, sure, I believe you.
Of course.

39:43.382 --> 39:46.761
Thank goodness. Everyone thinks
I lie all the time, but I don't.

39:46.761 --> 39:48.220
I know.

39:48.220 --> 39:50.931
Now try and close your eyes
and get some sleep, okay?

39:50.931 --> 39:51.891
Okay.

39:53.309 --> 39:54.352
Close your eyes.

39:58.481 --> 40:01.609
[DOG BARKING]

40:28.469 --> 40:34.600
[BARKING CONTINUES]

41:07.049 --> 41:09.176
[DOOR CREAKING]

41:53.804 --> 41:54.805
[DOOR SHUTS]

41:56.223 --> 41:58.893
[CREAKING]

41:58.893 --> 42:00.227
Is anybody there?

42:17.703 --> 42:18.454
[DOOR CREAKING]

43:36.949 --> 43:41.912
[INDISTINCT EERIE VOICE]

44:04.602 --> 44:09.148
[SCREAMS]

45:21.970 --> 45:25.432
[SCREAMING]

45:28.560 --> 45:30.521
Martha. Are you hurt?

45:35.025 --> 45:38.028
The doll. The doll is in there.

45:55.671 --> 46:00.676
422, 422 here. Lieutenant's
already on location

46:14.148 --> 46:15.941
I'm done here, Ferguson.

46:15.941 --> 46:18.277
I'll see you tomorrow
after the autopsy.

46:18.277 --> 46:19.862
Thank you, Doctor.
I'll see you tomorrow.

46:31.623 --> 46:33.083
How's your sister doing?

46:33.083 --> 46:36.378
She's still in shock. We had to
give her a tranquilizer.

46:36.378 --> 46:39.715
I'll have to question her
as soon as she's able.

46:39.715 --> 46:41.300
Of course.

46:41.300 --> 46:44.428
There's something you people
don't know about this place.

46:44.428 --> 46:46.013
A terrible crime
was committed here

46:46.013 --> 46:47.055
about 20 years ago.

46:48.849 --> 46:53.395
Double murder. Husband and wife.
Mr. and Mrs. Baker.

46:53.395 --> 46:55.355
- They lived here?
-They did.

46:55.355 --> 46:57.065
WOMAN: Lieutenant?

46:57.065 --> 46:57.816
Excuse me.

47:06.784 --> 47:10.621
They found him butchered,
one afternoon, in May, 1967.

47:10.621 --> 47:14.374
I was on the case then
so I remember it well.

47:14.374 --> 47:15.793
Did you find the murderer?

47:15.793 --> 47:18.921
No, it was one of the unsolved,
I'm afraid.

47:18.921 --> 47:21.131
Just like
the death of the little girl.

47:21.131 --> 47:22.674
Little girl?

47:22.674 --> 47:25.302
Yeah, the 11 year old
daughter, Henrietta.

47:25.302 --> 47:27.930
First we listed her as missing.

47:27.930 --> 47:29.973
- Then . ..
-And then?

47:29.973 --> 47:31.475
Then we found her
down in the cellar.

47:31.475 --> 47:33.560
Someone locked her in.

47:33.560 --> 47:36.980
She was dead, though
there were no marks on her.

47:36.980 --> 47:39.900
No signs of violence.
A total mystery.

47:39.900 --> 47:41.360
And since then?

47:41.360 --> 47:43.362
Since then
the house has been shut up,

47:43.362 --> 47:45.405
left just as it was.

47:45.405 --> 47:47.407
And nobody wanted
to live here any more.

47:47.407 --> 47:49.701
Who owns the house now?

47:49.701 --> 47:51.036
The county.

47:51.036 --> 47:55.123
Strange, Tina saw a little girl
near Jim's body.

47:55.123 --> 47:58.085
Tina has a tendency
to make things up.

47:58.085 --> 48:00.671
Folks like to see ghosts
in every dark corner.

48:00.671 --> 48:02.339
There's one thing, though.

48:02.339 --> 48:04.132
If you people
weren't trespassing,

48:04.132 --> 48:05.717
none of this would've happened.

48:05.717 --> 48:08.762
Valkos was bound to go off
his rocker sooner or later.

48:08.762 --> 48:11.431
- You think he killed Jim?
-There's no one else.

48:11.431 --> 48:13.016
County pays him
to keep an eye on the place.

48:13.016 --> 48:14.977
They subsidize him.

48:14.977 --> 48:17.271
You see, he used to be
in a state mental hospital.

48:17.271 --> 48:19.773
And in his twisted mind,

48:19.773 --> 48:22.651
your brother must've looked
like a thief or worse.

48:22.651 --> 48:23.569
So he hit him with a fan.

48:23.569 --> 48:24.987
But he had an ax.

48:24.987 --> 48:28.615
Well, in any case,
he won't get far, don't worry.

48:28.615 --> 48:30.617
We'll see to it that he doesn't
hurt anyone any more.

48:45.674 --> 48:47.467
You didn't buy it either,
did you?

48:47.467 --> 48:48.760
Ferguson's full of shit.

48:48.760 --> 48:50.012
He ought to be helping

48:50.012 --> 48:51.889
little old ladies
across the street.

48:51.889 --> 48:55.934
I'm positive Tina wasn't lying
about the little girl.

48:55.934 --> 48:58.604
Now don't forget the picture
that we found in the trunk.

48:58.604 --> 49:01.481
She could've seen it too, maybe,
just imagined the rest.

49:01.481 --> 49:04.401
- Do you really think so?
-No.

49:04.401 --> 49:06.528
So what can we do, Paul?

49:06.528 --> 49:08.113
How should I know?

49:08.113 --> 49:10.949
It's all just
one big horrible mess.

49:10.949 --> 49:12.951
But since the police
are deaf and blind,

49:12.951 --> 49:14.244
I guess we're just on our own.

49:18.540 --> 49:20.792
- How's Tina, Mark?
-She's still asleep.

49:23.629 --> 49:25.464
Listen, there's something
I want to try.

49:25.464 --> 49:27.758
Only I need my computer.

49:27.758 --> 49:29.051
Martha and I
are gonna go back to Boston.

49:31.094 --> 49:34.014
You guys should
leave this place right away.

49:34.014 --> 49:35.182
We"ll be gone
in a couple of hours.

49:35.182 --> 49:35.933
All we have to do is pack up.

49:40.103 --> 49:41.104
Okay.

50:00.707 --> 50:05.253
[INDISTINCT EERIE VOICE]

50:14.012 --> 50:15.514
Why don't you just drop it?

50:15.514 --> 50:18.392
You'll never decipher
the words of the damn song.

50:18.392 --> 50:20.978
Okay, okay. The simple fact
that the computer doesn't know,

50:20.978 --> 50:22.270
proves that I'm right.

50:22.270 --> 50:23.855
Oh, yeah.

50:23.855 --> 50:26.525
Don't you see? Those voices
had no logical explanation.

50:26.525 --> 50:27.693
We picked up

50:27.693 --> 50:29.903
a telepathic message
on the radio.

50:29.903 --> 50:31.905
You can't know what's gonna
happen in the future.

50:31.905 --> 50:33.240
Yes, you can.

50:33.240 --> 50:35.367
Cases of precognition
have occurred.

50:35.367 --> 50:37.077
Since when are you
into that stuff?

50:37.077 --> 50:39.162
About 45 minutes.

50:39.162 --> 50:41.164
I checked out this book
while you were in the shower.

50:41.164 --> 50:41.915
Oh?

50:42.958 --> 50:44.710
Remember Jack the Ripper?

50:44.710 --> 50:47.254
The psychopath
who butchered seven women?

50:47.254 --> 50:48.839
Yeah?

50:48.839 --> 50:50.507
So there was
this Anglican priest

50:50.507 --> 50:51.967
who had a vision
of the last murder

50:51.967 --> 50:53.051
a few days before it happened.

50:53.051 --> 50:55.846
- Where?
-In the street car.

50:55.846 --> 50:57.931
The murder took place
in a street car.

50:57.931 --> 50:59.725
No, the minister
was on a street car

50:59.725 --> 51:01.184
when he suddenly had the vision.

51:01.184 --> 51:02.477
Are you getting stupid
or something?

51:02.477 --> 51:03.979
Look who's talking.

51:03.979 --> 51:05.731
Did you learn all that
while I was washing my hair?

51:05.731 --> 51:06.857
Would you be serious?

51:06.857 --> 51:08.400
Would you climb off
your high horse?

51:08.400 --> 51:10.277
You know something,
I've had enough. Good bye.

51:24.374 --> 51:28.503
[MUSIC PLAYING]

51:31.465 --> 51:36.762
[NURSERY RHYME PLAYING]

51:57.908 --> 52:00.535
Hello.
Lieutenant Ferguson, please.

52:00.535 --> 52:03.580
Oh, it's you, sir.
No, this is Paul Rogers.

52:05.082 --> 52:06.041
Pardon?

52:07.125 --> 52:08.126
You haven't caught him yet?

52:11.588 --> 52:13.632
Lieutenant,
I was just wondering,

52:15.425 --> 52:17.135
what did Sam Baker do
for a living?

52:20.055 --> 52:20.806
Uh-huh?

52:23.058 --> 52:23.809
Just outside of town.

52:25.811 --> 52:28.105
I see. Right.

52:29.981 --> 52:31.858
Thank you. Bye.

52:35.028 --> 52:36.071
A funeral home?

53:07.727 --> 53:13.525
[SCREAMING]

53:18.446 --> 53:19.781
Some joke, huh?

53:19.781 --> 53:22.826
You asshole. Who are you?
What are you doing here?

53:22.826 --> 53:24.077
My name is Pepe.

53:24.077 --> 53:25.787
Just looking for a place
to spend the night.

53:25.787 --> 53:28.456
Froze my buns off last night.

53:28.456 --> 53:30.167
You in the camper over there?

53:30.167 --> 53:32.252
Forget it, we're leaving.

53:32.252 --> 53:34.504
Well, okay. Hey, want some?

53:34.504 --> 53:36.756
- No.
-Come on, it's good for you.

53:36.756 --> 53:38.425
Okay.

53:38.425 --> 53:40.635
Heard nobody stays
in this house any more.

53:40.635 --> 53:42.971
Is that true?
Great.

53:42.971 --> 53:44.890
You're not gonna sleep in there.

53:44.890 --> 53:47.517
Sure, why not?
A roof's a roof.

53:47.517 --> 53:48.935
You wanna come
help me explore it?

53:50.896 --> 53:53.315
Okay. So long.

53:56.151 --> 53:58.111
Tina! Tina!

53:58.111 --> 54:00.989
[HONKING]

54:00.989 --> 54:02.782
Come on, Tina.
Hurry up, we're going.

54:12.542 --> 54:14.502
[CAR STALLING]

54:18.548 --> 54:21.092
- What's going on?
-I don't know.

54:21.092 --> 54:22.844
The distributor's been
giving me some problems.

55:23.280 --> 55:25.198
Boy, I hope
this is real silver.

55:48.763 --> 55:53.226
[BANGING]

55:55.645 --> 55:57.272
Who's there?

55:57.272 --> 56:00.066
[BANGING CONTINUES]

57:14.682 --> 57:16.309
You could say something,
you know.

57:16.309 --> 57:17.811
You haven't said a word
since we left Boston.

57:17.811 --> 57:19.020
Leave me alone.

57:19.020 --> 57:20.522
Just hurry.

57:20.522 --> 57:22.107
I don't wanna sit here
like an idiot all day long.

57:32.450 --> 57:34.411
- Anybody here?
-I'm in the back.

57:52.387 --> 57:53.346
Looks alive, doesn't she?

57:55.056 --> 57:57.684
You should've seen her
when they brought her in.

57:57.684 --> 58:00.353
Poor old thing.
She was hit by a bus.

58:05.817 --> 58:08.319
I am at your complete disposal.

58:08.319 --> 58:11.156
And may I offer you
my sincerest condolences.

58:13.450 --> 58:16.744
No, I just wanted
some information.

58:16.744 --> 58:18.538
Yes.

58:18.538 --> 58:22.459
About 20 years ago, did you know
a Mr. Sam Baker?

58:22.459 --> 58:23.334
Why do you ask?

58:24.627 --> 58:27.380
Just curious. Did you know him?

58:27.380 --> 58:28.923
Well, of course, I did.

58:28.923 --> 58:31.050
I used to work
for Sam Baker back then.

58:31.050 --> 58:34.512
And I took over the company
after his death.

58:34.512 --> 58:36.723
We didn't have this place here.

58:36.723 --> 58:40.143
We had a little place
near the cemetery.

58:40.143 --> 58:42.103
Can you tell me
anything about him?

58:42.103 --> 58:44.522
Sam was a good man.

58:44.522 --> 58:47.442
He didn't deserve
the end he came to.

58:47.442 --> 58:49.903
- Even if?
-Even if what?

58:49.903 --> 58:51.613
Well, let's just say

58:51.613 --> 58:55.575
I didn't approve
of some of his practices.

58:55.575 --> 58:56.993
For instance?

58:56.993 --> 58:59.204
He had a real bad habit.

58:59.204 --> 59:03.708
He used to take little things
off the deceased, you know.

59:03.708 --> 59:04.876
Nothing important.

59:06.503 --> 59:09.130
A locket. A little necklace.
Maybe a pen.

59:12.008 --> 59:15.887
Can you recall
any particular object?

59:15.887 --> 59:18.723
- It's been a long time.
-Yeah, sure.

59:20.433 --> 59:24.521
Wait a minute. I remember.

59:24.521 --> 59:29.275
It happened just before he died.
We had an argument about it.

59:29.275 --> 59:31.736
Sam took a doll
that was supposed to be buried

59:31.736 --> 59:33.404
with the deceased owner.

59:33.404 --> 59:36.032
He said his little girl
would love it.

59:36.032 --> 59:37.534
Did you say a doll?

59:37.534 --> 59:39.577
I got really mad that time.

59:39.577 --> 59:42.413
It wasn't valuable or anything.
That wasn't the point.

59:42.413 --> 59:45.542
You can talk to Old Harvey
the cemetery custodian about it.

59:45.542 --> 59:47.168
I'll bet he remembers.

59:47.168 --> 59:48.753
How far is the cemetery
from here?

59:48.753 --> 59:50.213
Less than two miles.

59:50.213 --> 59:52.674
Right after you cross
the highway, on your left.

59:52.674 --> 59:53.925
Thank you, Mr. Gaffey.

59:53.925 --> 59:55.218
I don't know
that he'll be there today.

59:55.218 --> 59:56.177
It's Saturday.

01:00:27.375 --> 01:00:28.376
[DOOR BANGS]

01:00:31.004 --> 01:00:33.089
You better get on
out of here, Valkos.

01:00:33.089 --> 01:00:34.882
The police are looking
all over the place for you

01:00:34.882 --> 01:00:36.092
and I don't want any trouble.

01:00:36.092 --> 01:00:38.052
What did
that son of a bitch want?

01:00:38.052 --> 01:00:39.554
Nothing. Just some information.

01:00:39.554 --> 01:00:41.097
You're all on this together.

01:00:41.097 --> 01:00:43.474
All transgressors of God's will.

01:00:43.474 --> 01:00:45.935
That's foolishness.
You just get on out of here.

01:00:45.935 --> 01:00:48.104
You're in cahoots with them,
you scum.

01:00:48.104 --> 01:00:51.232
You get out of here, right now
and I won't tell anybody

01:00:51.232 --> 01:00:51.983
I've seen you, Valkos.

01:01:04.704 --> 01:01:07.373
No. No!

01:01:10.376 --> 01:01:11.210
[SCREAMS]

01:01:27.518 --> 01:01:30.813
[GROANING]

01:01:54.837 --> 01:01:58.216
No. No.

01:02:06.808 --> 01:02:07.934
No.

01:02:07.934 --> 01:02:10.603
[SCREAMING]

01:02:12.855 --> 01:02:15.858
Okay, Doc, what have you got?

01:02:15.858 --> 01:02:17.610
Well, I've done the autopsy.

01:02:17.610 --> 01:02:18.903
You know, in all my years,

01:02:18.903 --> 01:02:21.698
I've never seen a case
stranger than this.

01:02:21.698 --> 01:02:23.950
- I just...
-Oh, not you, too.

01:02:23.950 --> 01:02:25.451
Just got a call
from one of the kids.

01:02:25.451 --> 01:02:27.370
The HAM radio operator.

01:02:27.370 --> 01:02:28.871
He wanted to know

01:02:28.871 --> 01:02:29.789
what poor Sam Baker did
for a living.

01:02:31.708 --> 01:02:33.084
I wonder what those kids
have dreamed up now.

01:02:34.877 --> 01:02:38.423
Look, I-I just can't go along

01:02:38.423 --> 01:02:40.883
with your reconstruction
of this case.

01:02:40.883 --> 01:02:42.135
What are you saying, Doc?

01:02:42.135 --> 01:02:44.470
The wound appears to be
a clean incision.

01:02:44.470 --> 01:02:47.598
There are no torn tissues,
no bruises.

01:02:47.598 --> 01:02:50.268
And further more,
the blade severed the artery

01:02:50.268 --> 01:02:53.229
on an upward angle
coming from below.

01:02:53.229 --> 01:02:54.689
So?

01:02:54.689 --> 01:02:56.774
That boy
could not have been killed

01:02:56.774 --> 01:03:00.445
by a blow from someone using
the fan as a weapon.

01:03:00.445 --> 01:03:03.573
The only hypothesis that
holds up scientifically at all.

01:03:03.573 --> 01:03:06.868
One of the fan blades broke off
while it was running.

01:03:06.868 --> 01:03:09.787
Centrifugal force sent the blade
flying through the air

01:03:09.787 --> 01:03:12.582
and it slices
through the boy's throat.

01:03:12.582 --> 01:03:13.750
From an upward angle.

01:03:15.626 --> 01:03:16.335
Are you joking?

01:03:17.545 --> 01:03:18.921
You know as well as I do

01:03:18.921 --> 01:03:21.007
that the fan
is not in running order.

01:03:21.007 --> 01:03:22.800
I mean, it just doesn't
even have a motor.

01:03:22.800 --> 01:03:25.553
How can it work without a motor,
without electrical current?

01:03:29.432 --> 01:03:32.935
If you recall, 20 years ago,
when the Bakers were killed,

01:03:32.935 --> 01:03:36.314
we had a lot of questions
we didn't have any answers for.

01:03:36.314 --> 01:03:39.275
And people were wondering
a long time after that.

01:03:39.275 --> 01:03:40.943
To hell with them.

01:03:40.943 --> 01:03:43.196
People are susceptible,
they are gullible.

01:03:43.196 --> 01:03:45.531
And don't you forget about
the Salem Witch trials.

01:03:45.531 --> 01:03:47.575
This is good old
Massachusetts, Doc.

01:03:47.575 --> 01:03:48.993
That's neither here nor there.

01:03:50.912 --> 01:03:52.747
Have you picked up Valkos yet?

01:03:52.747 --> 01:03:54.582
It's just a matter of time.

01:03:54.582 --> 01:03:56.959
We set up roadblocks
throughout the entire county.

01:03:56.959 --> 01:03:58.461
We should be quick about it.

01:03:58.461 --> 01:04:00.338
I've got a bad feeling
about this.

01:04:00.338 --> 01:04:03.966
I've got the feeling
that the worst is yet to come.

01:04:03.966 --> 01:04:05.218
It's those kids.

01:04:05.218 --> 01:04:06.803
Stop worrying.

01:04:06.803 --> 01:04:08.638
They're not
in any danger any more.

01:04:08.638 --> 01:04:09.722
They left the house by now.

01:04:21.609 --> 01:04:23.778
I did so see him
going into the house.

01:04:23.778 --> 01:04:27.073
He was this weird guy
and he had this skeleton arm.

01:04:27.073 --> 01:04:28.950
- He had what?
-A skeleton arm.

01:04:28.950 --> 01:04:30.076
Are you deaf?

01:04:30.076 --> 01:04:31.285
Oh, come on, Tina,
give me a break.

01:04:31.285 --> 01:04:32.912
He did and I saw it.

01:04:32.912 --> 01:04:34.163
You never believe
anything I say.

01:04:34.163 --> 01:04:35.540
- That...
-will you guys just cut it out?

01:04:37.500 --> 01:04:38.501
Wait right here.

01:04:50.638 --> 01:04:53.474
Look, there's nobody in there.
It's okay.

01:04:54.976 --> 01:04:58.104
I swear I saw him, Mark.
I'm not kidding.

01:04:58.104 --> 01:04:59.730
Sure, Tina.

01:04:59.730 --> 01:05:01.858
Listen, why don't you go inside
and watch some television?

01:05:08.656 --> 01:05:10.199
What can you do?

01:05:10.199 --> 01:05:12.493
She's been making things up
ever since she could talk.

01:05:12.493 --> 01:05:14.662
But this time
she's gone too far.

01:05:14.662 --> 01:05:17.081
No, I think she's in shock
over Jim.

01:05:17.081 --> 01:05:19.208
I mean, he was the only one
who could really handle her.

01:05:21.711 --> 01:05:23.129
Listen, about Jim,

01:05:24.964 --> 01:05:29.010
I don't believe in ghosts and
spirits and that kind of stuff.

01:05:29.010 --> 01:05:30.469
This is almost the 21st century.

01:05:32.138 --> 01:05:35.725
Let's face it.
That crazy caretaker killed him.

01:05:35.725 --> 01:05:38.227
But if it was him, Susan,
why didn't he use the ax?

01:05:39.687 --> 01:05:41.188
Okay, but what proof
have you got?

01:05:41.188 --> 01:05:43.190
Your stupid sister's story
about seeing some ghost

01:05:43.190 --> 01:05:44.650
of a kid dressed in white?

01:05:44.650 --> 01:05:47.194
What about the message Paul
picked up on his radio

01:05:47.194 --> 01:05:49.488
two days before Jim was killed?

01:05:49.488 --> 01:05:50.823
And that's on tape.

01:05:51.866 --> 01:05:53.534
How do you explain that?

01:05:53.534 --> 01:05:54.702
Well, how the hell
should I know?

01:06:00.458 --> 01:06:03.586
MARK: I know, I'm sorry.

01:06:07.798 --> 01:06:10.384
Let's get our butts
out of here, Mark.

01:06:21.646 --> 01:06:23.147
You could've sat down
and eaten something

01:06:23.147 --> 01:06:24.482
instead of rushing me like that.

01:06:24.482 --> 01:06:25.816
I wasn't hungry.

01:06:25.816 --> 01:06:29.153
Neither was I.
I just wanted a minute to think.

01:06:29.153 --> 01:06:30.988
I'm scared, Paul.

01:06:30.988 --> 01:06:33.658
I just can't wait to talk
to that cemetery custodian.

01:06:33.658 --> 01:06:35.660
What do you hope to learn?

01:06:35.660 --> 01:06:37.662
I don't know. I just can't get
that doll out of my mind.

01:06:40.039 --> 01:06:44.001
I saw it. It looked evil.
I'll never forget that look.

01:07:08.859 --> 01:07:10.111
He's still in here.

01:07:12.446 --> 01:07:13.364
I just know it.

01:07:15.282 --> 01:07:16.200
And so is she.

01:07:39.432 --> 01:07:41.475
[EERIE MUSIC PLAYING]

01:07:46.814 --> 01:07:49.775
Here you go. Do you mind?
I'm gonna go take a shower.

01:07:49.775 --> 01:07:53.320
Sorry, but you can't.
Forgot to fill the tank.

01:07:53.320 --> 01:07:56.407
Listen, I'll be back
in about half hour, all right?

01:07:56.407 --> 01:07:57.825
Sure, you don't need a mechanic?

01:07:57.825 --> 01:08:00.578
All I need is a part.
I can do the rest myself.

01:08:02.496 --> 01:08:04.498
Listen, keep an eye on Tina
for me, okay.

01:08:04.498 --> 01:08:06.542
She'll be okay. She's in denial.

01:08:43.662 --> 01:08:48.167
[INDISTINCT EERIE VOICE]

01:08:59.053 --> 01:09:00.136
Where are you?

01:09:04.558 --> 01:09:05.810
Come out and let me see you.

01:09:07.645 --> 01:09:09.188
Where are you?

01:09:09.188 --> 01:09:10.523
[MUSIC STOPS]

01:09:36.048 --> 01:09:38.968
[TINA SCREAMING]

01:09:38.968 --> 01:09:41.720
[POP MUSIC PLAYING ON WALKMAN]

01:10:35.316 --> 01:10:36.317
[SCREAMS]

01:10:49.288 --> 01:10:51.123
[SCREAMS]

01:11:00.799 --> 01:11:03.802
Oh, Tina. Tina, thank God
you're all right.

01:11:05.512 --> 01:11:06.805
Forgive me.

01:11:07.848 --> 01:11:09.683
[EERIE MUSIC PLAYING]

01:11:09.683 --> 01:11:13.646
[INDISTINCT EERIE VOICE]

01:11:37.670 --> 01:11:39.505
No, you stay here.

01:11:39.505 --> 01:11:42.299
Better yet, raise Mark
on the radio. 1790.

01:11:42.299 --> 01:11:44.093
God only knows where he is now.

01:11:44.093 --> 01:11:46.428
I'm just afraid they're still
at that damned house.

01:11:46.428 --> 01:11:48.180
And if they are,
they're in real danger.

01:11:48.180 --> 01:11:50.391
They've gotta get out of there
right away. Now.

01:11:50.391 --> 01:11:51.392
Right.

01:12:06.782 --> 01:12:08.867
[STATIC]

01:12:11.161 --> 01:12:12.162
Mark, are you there?

01:12:15.124 --> 01:12:15.874
Come in, Mark.

01:12:18.335 --> 01:12:19.336
Mark.

01:12:21.672 --> 01:12:24.383
-[KNOCKING AT DOOR]
-PAUL: Harvey.

01:12:24.383 --> 01:12:25.134
Harvey.

01:12:26.427 --> 01:12:27.177
Mr. Harvey.

01:12:35.477 --> 01:12:36.478
Mr. Harvey.

01:12:37.980 --> 01:12:38.981
Mr. Harvey, please.

01:12:40.190 --> 01:12:41.358
Sir.

01:12:41.358 --> 01:12:43.360
[MUMBLES]

01:12:45.612 --> 01:12:47.072
Mr. Harvey.

01:12:47.072 --> 01:12:47.781
Mark.

01:12:49.241 --> 01:12:49.950
Mark, please come in.

01:13:10.095 --> 01:13:14.933
[LOUD MUSIC PLAYING]

01:13:20.022 --> 01:13:21.482
MARTHA OVER RADIO:
<i>Mark. Mark.</i>

01:13:24.109 --> 01:13:25.277
I copy. Go ahead.

01:13:25.277 --> 01:13:27.988
Paul wants to know
where you are now.

01:13:27.988 --> 01:13:30.115
Right next to the house
where you left us. Why?

01:13:30.115 --> 01:13:31.992
<i>You got to get out of there
right away.</i>

01:13:31.992 --> 01:13:34.036
<i>Your lives are in danger.</i>

01:13:34.036 --> 01:13:36.622
Why? What happened?
What has Paul come up with?

01:13:36.622 --> 01:13:38.290
He'll tell you everything
himself.

01:13:38.290 --> 01:13:39.750
Just get moving
as fast as you can.

01:13:44.630 --> 01:13:47.299
Martha. Martha, answer me.
What is it?

01:13:49.760 --> 01:13:50.511
Paul!

01:13:52.638 --> 01:13:53.639
Help!

01:14:58.245 --> 01:15:02.583
Bad things happen to old souls
that can't find peace.

01:15:02.583 --> 01:15:04.460
I warned Sam.

01:15:04.460 --> 01:15:05.377
Don't offend the dead.

01:15:07.004 --> 01:15:08.046
That's sacrilege.

01:15:09.923 --> 01:15:11.550
This has been going on 20 years,
you know.

01:15:13.135 --> 01:15:14.928
- There's been other victims.
-You're kidding.

01:15:16.430 --> 01:15:20.601
Five years ago,
kid from Mount Claire.

01:15:20.601 --> 01:15:22.436
Disappeared.

01:15:22.436 --> 01:15:25.439
Last he was seen
walking by that old house.

01:15:25.439 --> 01:15:26.982
Dropped out of sight.

01:15:26.982 --> 01:15:30.110
Have you ever seen
the little girl Henrietta?

01:15:32.196 --> 01:15:33.489
Uh, yes.

01:15:35.491 --> 01:15:37.367
One night, I was walking
by that old house.

01:15:38.911 --> 01:15:40.412
May God preserve us.

01:16:24.831 --> 01:16:26.750
[SCREAMS]

01:17:09.585 --> 01:17:10.502
MARK: Susan!

01:17:17.092 --> 01:17:21.847
Susan! Tina! Answer me!

01:17:31.815 --> 01:17:32.566
Martha.

01:17:50.250 --> 01:17:52.127
Martha! Martha!

01:17:53.086 --> 01:17:54.087
Martha!

01:17:55.505 --> 01:17:56.506
Where are you?

01:18:24.701 --> 01:18:27.829
Paul! Get me out of here!

01:18:28.914 --> 01:18:31.708
I can't stand it here any more.

01:18:31.708 --> 01:18:36.046
Help! Help! Help!

01:18:37.255 --> 01:18:40.342
Someone get me out of here!

01:18:40.342 --> 01:18:44.930
Help! Help! No!

01:18:46.348 --> 01:18:48.975
Someone get me out of here!

01:18:48.975 --> 01:18:51.853
Help! Help!

01:18:52.688 --> 01:18:53.689
No!

01:19:08.036 --> 01:19:09.913
[MARTHA SCREAMING]

01:19:09.913 --> 01:19:12.165
MARTHA: Get me out of here.

01:19:12.165 --> 01:19:14.418
I can't stand it in here at all.

01:19:14.418 --> 01:19:16.253
Someone get me out of here.

01:19:19.965 --> 01:19:22.050
Someone get me out of here.

01:19:32.436 --> 01:19:33.395
Help!

01:19:35.355 --> 01:19:37.566
Martha. Martha.

01:19:52.205 --> 01:19:53.165
- Martha.
-Paul.

01:19:55.417 --> 01:19:56.626
It's all right now. I'm here.

01:20:22.027 --> 01:20:22.736
Susan!

01:20:31.119 --> 01:20:32.913
[MUSIC PLAYING]

01:20:32.913 --> 01:20:36.833
[INDISTINCT EERIE VOICE]

01:20:40.712 --> 01:20:43.256
[DRIPPING]

01:21:40.939 --> 01:21:42.482
Oh, my God.

01:21:57.664 --> 01:22:01.293
[SCREAMING]

01:22:08.592 --> 01:22:12.929
[SCREAMS ECHOING]

01:22:39.122 --> 01:22:43.084
[SCREAMING
AND WAILING CONTINUES]

01:22:43.084 --> 01:22:46.171
[EVIL LAUGHTER]

01:24:10.422 --> 01:24:14.134
[MARK GASPING AND GROANING]

01:25:50.772 --> 01:25:52.690
Let me out of here.

01:25:54.984 --> 01:25:55.735
You'll feel better.

01:26:01.241 --> 01:26:04.494
Oh, Paul. I saw death.

01:26:04.494 --> 01:26:06.371
[SUSAN SCREAMING]

01:26:08.123 --> 01:26:08.873
Wait.

01:26:14.921 --> 01:26:16.381
<i>SUSAN:
Help! Help!</i>

01:26:17.590 --> 01:26:18.466
Susan.

01:26:19.551 --> 01:26:21.261
<i>Let me out of here.</i>

01:27:24.365 --> 01:27:28.703
[BARKING]

01:27:40.298 --> 01:27:44.052
[INDISTINCT EERIE VOICE]

01:29:50.303 --> 01:29:52.889
[THUNDERCLAP]

01:30:37.475 --> 01:30:38.976
Right, Henry.

01:30:38.976 --> 01:30:40.812
I'll keep the press away
until you get here.

01:30:42.647 --> 01:30:44.023
What was that?

01:30:44.023 --> 01:30:45.900
That's all nonsense.

01:30:45.900 --> 01:30:48.111
The killer committed suicide.

01:30:48.111 --> 01:30:49.487
We found him
hanging from a tree

01:30:49.487 --> 01:30:51.531
about two hours ago
in the cemetery.

01:30:53.157 --> 01:30:56.619
Sure, Henry.
There's not a thing wrong.

01:30:56.619 --> 01:30:57.578
I'll see you later.

01:31:01.666 --> 01:31:05.002
I know. I know. But that was
the District Attorney.

01:31:05.002 --> 01:31:08.256
What can I tell him?
The truth?

01:31:08.256 --> 01:31:11.509
- Why not?
-All hell would've broken loose.

01:31:11.509 --> 01:31:14.929
Listen,
people just wanna be reassured.

01:31:14.929 --> 01:31:18.141
Believe me. I mean,
they don't wanna know

01:31:18.141 --> 01:31:21.394
about ghosts and curses
and whatnot.

01:31:31.904 --> 01:31:32.864
Can I go now?

01:31:35.616 --> 01:31:37.660
I know how you feel.

01:31:37.660 --> 01:31:40.496
But you're gonna have to learn
to live with this on your own.

01:31:40.496 --> 01:31:42.373
Because you can't talk
about it with anyone.

01:31:42.373 --> 01:31:44.667
They'll only think you're crazy.

01:31:44.667 --> 01:31:46.878
I know, you're right.

01:31:46.878 --> 01:31:50.798
I just wanna get out of here.
As far away as I can.

01:31:50.798 --> 01:31:52.425
I understand.

01:31:52.425 --> 01:31:55.052
Don't worry. You'll never see
Henrietta again.

01:31:55.052 --> 01:31:56.679
Who was she?

01:31:56.679 --> 01:31:58.473
Just an ordinary little girl.

01:31:58.473 --> 01:32:01.100
Until her father
gave her that doll.

01:32:01.100 --> 01:32:02.727
And that's where it all started.

01:32:19.243 --> 01:32:19.952
How do you feel?

01:32:21.162 --> 01:32:22.747
Much better.

01:32:22.747 --> 01:32:25.541
You'll see. I'll be as good
as new before the week's out.

01:33:05.831 --> 01:33:06.958
Martha!
